  Title: The Complete Works of Chuang Tzu
  Translator: Burton Watson
Title: The Great And Venerable Teacher
---
Tzu-kung returned and reported to Confucius what had happened. "What
sort of men are they anyway?" he asked. "They pay no attention to
proper behavior, disregard their personal appearance and, without so
much as changing the expression on their faces, sing in the very
presence of the corpse! I can think of no name for them! What sort of
men are they?"
